Vectors¶

a+b
Out[4]:

In [5]:
a-b
Out[5]:
array([-4, -2])

Out[6]:
array([4, 6])

a.T
Out[7]:

Matrix Addition and Subtraction¶

In [14]:
A = np.array([[3, 9, -1, 2], [8, 2, 0, -7], [-4, 7, 9, 2]])
B = np.array([[-1, 0, 2, 4], [-3, 1, 0, 6], [7, 0, -3, 4]])
A+B
Out[14]:
array([[ 2,  9,  1,  6],
       [ 5,  3,  0, -1],
       [ 3,  7,  6,  6]])
In [15]:
A-B
Out[15]:
array([[  4,   9,  -3,  -2],
       [ 11,   1,   0, -13],
       [-11,   7,  12,  -2]])

Matrix Multiplication¶

In [16]:
A = np.array([[3, 9], [-1, 2], [8, 2], [0, -7]])
B = np.array([[2, 3], [-1, 4]])
np.dot(A, B)
Out[16]:
array([[ -3,  45],
       [ -4,   5],
       [ 14,  32],
       [  7, -28]])

System of Linear Equations¶

In [17]:
a = np.array([[2, 1, -2], [1, -3, 1], [4, -1, -2]]) ### Coefficients
b = np.array([-3, 8, 3]) ### Constants
np.linalg.solve(a, b)
Out[17]:
array([ 2., -1.,  3.])
In [18]:
a = np.array([[1, -2, 3], [-1, 3, 0], [2, -5, 5]]) ### Coefficients
b = np.array([9, -4, 17]) ### Constants
np.linalg.solve(a, b)
Out[18]:
array([ 1., -1.,  2.])

Part - 3¶

System of Equations - No Solution¶

In [19]:
a = np.array([[1, -1, 2], [1, 0, 1], [2, -3, 5]]) ### Coefficients
b = np.array([4, 6, 4]) ### Constants
try:
    np.linalg.solve(a, b) ### No solution - will result in Singular Matrix error
except np.linalg.LinAlgError as le:
    print('ERROR:', le)

ERROR: Singular matrix

Inverse of a Matrix¶

In [20]:
A = np.array([[1, 4], [-1, -3]])
np.linalg.inv(A)
Out[20]:
array([[-3., -4.],
       [ 1.,  1.]])
In [21]:
A = np.array([[1, -1, 0], [1, 0, -1], [-6, 2, 3]])
np.linalg.inv(A)
Out[21]:
array([[-2., -3., -1.],
       [-3., -3., -1.],
       [-2., -4., -1.]])

Part - 4¶

Eigen Decomposition¶

In [23]:
A = np.array([[2, 2], [5, -1]])
L, V = np.linalg.eig(A)
L, V
Out[23]:
(array([ 4., -3.]),
 array([[ 0.7071, -0.3714],
        [ 0.7071,  0.9285]]))
In [24]:
A = np.array([[-2, -4, 2], [-2, 1, 2], [4, 2, 5]])
L, V = np.linalg.eig(A)
L, V
Out[24]:
(array([-5.,  3.,  6.]),
 array([[ 0.8165,  0.5345,  0.0584],
        [ 0.4082, -0.8018,  0.3505],
        [-0.4082, -0.2673,  0.9347]]))

Singular Value Decomposition¶

In [26]:
A = np.array([[1, -1, 3], [3, 1, 1]])
U, S, VT = np.linalg.svd(A)
U, S, VT
Out[26]:
(array([[-0.7071, -0.7071],
        [-0.7071,  0.7071]]),
 array([4.    , 2.4495]),
 array([[-0.7071,  0.    , -0.7071],
        [ 0.5774,  0.5774, -0.5774],
        [-0.4082,  0.8165,  0.4082]]))

Using SVD for Image Compression¶

In [27]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from PIL import Image
In [28]:
img = Image.open('tomcat.jpg')
plt.title('Original Image')
plt.imshow(img)
plt.show()
In [29]:
img = img.convert('LA')
img.size
Out[29]:
(1260, 852)
In [30]:
IMG = np.array(list(img.getdata(band=0)), float)
IMG.resize(img.size[1], img.size[0])
IMG.size, IMG.shape
Out[30]:
(1073520, (852, 1260))
In [31]:
plt.imshow(IMG, cmap='gray')
Out[31]:
<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x7f4b03d26d00>
In [32]:
U, s, VT = np.linalg.svd(IMG, full_matrices=False)
U.shape, s.shape, VT.shape
Out[32]:
((852, 852), (852,), (852, 1260))
In [33]:
S = np.diag(s)
In [34]:
r = 16
UR = U[:, :r]
SR = S[0:r, :r]
VTR = VT[:r, :]
UR.shape, SR.shape, VTR.shape
Out[34]:
((852, 16), (16, 16), (16, 1260))
In [35]:
NEW_IMG = np.matrix(UR) * SR * np.matrix(VTR)
plt.title('Rank = 16')
plt.imshow(NEW_IMG, cmap='gray')
plt.show()
In [36]:
r = 32
UR = U[:, :r]
SR = S[0:r, :r]
VTR = VT[:r, :]
UR.shape, SR.shape, VTR.shape
Out[36]:
((852, 32), (32, 32), (32, 1260))
In [37]:
NEW_IMG = np.matrix(UR) * SR * np.matrix(VTR)
plt.title('Rank = 32')
plt.imshow(NEW_IMG, cmap='gray')
plt.show()
In [38]:
r = 64
UR = U[:, :r]
SR = S[0:r, :r]
VTR = VT[:r, :]
UR.shape, SR.shape, VTR.shape
Out[38]:
((852, 64), (64, 64), (64, 1260))
In [39]:
NEW_IMG = np.matrix(UR) * SR * np.matrix(VTR)
plt.title('Rank = 64')
plt.imshow(NEW_IMG, cmap='gray')
plt.show()
In [42]:
actual_sz = img.size[0] * img.size[1]
new_sz = 64 * img.size[0] + 64 + 64 * img.size[1]
print('Image compression %0.2f percent' % (100 - new_sz/actual_sz * 100))

Image compression 87.40 percent
